		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Related technique showcased here: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1EnSQw9vkEU">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1EnSQw9vkEU</a><!-- m --> <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tgQNDB56gXQ">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tgQNDB56gXQ</a><!-- m --> (Sorry about the obtrusive watermarks.)<br />When the game calls the sound engine telling it to play song X, something intervenes and ignores the song, and instead, plays a MP3 corresponding to X through device Y. Sound effects still get played normally by the game.

		

